  <Docs>
    <summary>Describes a single variation axis of an OpenType variable font.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontVariationAxis` describes a single variation axis defined by an OpenType variable font.
Use <xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.VariationDesignParameters> or
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.GetVariationDesignParameters*> to retrieve the axes for a typeface.

To set a variation axis value, create an <xref:SkiaSharp.SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate>
with the axis <see cref="P:SkiaSharp.SKFontVariationAxis.Tag" /> and the desired value, then
pass the coordinates to <xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.Clone*>.
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
